{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:24:51.660166+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: ce907a77bdc824b30f8d9cc6bce388af0342e3fe)", "id": "lc_ce86d43a-cf5f-48e2-8147-4bbe7ec9ae9a"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import { useEffect } from \"react\";\nimport Logout from \"../components/auth/Logout\";\nimport Center from \"../components/utils/Center\";\n\nconst Home = (props) => {\n  useEffect(() => {}, []); // eslint-disable-line react-hooks/exhaustive-deps\n\n  return (\n    <Center>\n      <Logout />\n    </Center>\n  );\n};\n\nexport default Home;\n", "id": "lc_bfa9dea9-4f83-4070-905c-0ddc39c03ccc"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "324ab300-fe34-470a-8bc7-58215163d58c", "tool_call_id": "call_00_1EHmuXHjTVDviuqwUW6b5912", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:24:51.661292+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 5ff2a77dcd6c2b34f7c51407ef2e793c6cda06a1)", "id": "lc_9fa7a228-f41d-42d1-bb4e-59e315b3393b"}, {"type": "text", "text": "import { Box, Tab, Tabs } from \"@mui/material\";\nimport React from \"react\";\nimport { useSearchParams } from \"react-router-dom\";\nimport AuthContainer from \"../components/auth/AuthContainer\";\nimport Center from \"../components/utils/Center\";\n\nconst tabIdToURL = {\n  0: \"login\",\n  1: \"register\",\n};\n\nconst Login = (props) => {\n  // getting and setting URL params\n  const [searchParams, setSearchParams] = useSearchParams();\n\n  // get action from URL\n  const action = searchParams.get(\"action\") || \"login\";\n\n  // used to set initial state\n  let indexFromUrl = 0;\n  if (action === \"register\") {\n    indexFromUrl = 1;\n  }\n\n  // handle Tab Panel\n  const [value, setValue] = React.useState(indexFromUrl);\n\n  const handleChange = (event, newValue) => {\n    setValue(newValue);\n    const action = tabIdToURL[newValue];\n    setSearchParams({ action });\n  };\n\n  return (\n    <Center height={90}>\n      <Box\n        display={\"flex\"}\n        alignItems={\"center\"}\n        flexDirection={\"column\"}\n        boxShadow={2}\n        margin={3}\n      >\n        <Box sx={{ borderBottom: 1, borderColor: \"divider\", width: \"100%\" }}>\n          <Tabs value={value} onChange={handleChange} variant=\"fullWidth\">\n            <Tab sx={{ px: { lg: 20, xs: 6 } }} label=\"Login\" />\n            <Tab sx={{ px: { lg: 16, xs: 6 } }} label=\"Register\" />\n          </Tabs>\n        </Box>\n        {/* login */}\n        <TabPanel value={value} index={0}>\n          <AuthContainer />\n        </TabPanel>\n        {/* register */}\n        <TabPanel value={value} index={1}>\n          <AuthContainer />\n        </TabPanel>\n      </Box>\n    </Center>\n  );\n};\n\nconst TabPanel = ({ children, value, index }) => {\n  return (\n    <div role=\"tabpanel\" hidden={value !== index}>\n      {value === index && (\n        <Box sx={{ p: 3 }}>\n          <>{children}</>\n        </Box>\n      )}\n    </div>\n  );\n};\n\nexport default Login;\n", "id": "lc_dd386916-9e7d-4618-82a7-262586f6d7c6"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "d0515436-4106-4804-924a-9c10ef3ae8a4", "tool_call_id": "call_01_jCl2i5L4gOwBxtIAmS5F6126", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T04:25:05.331767+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "## Routing Configuration in This Starter\n\n### How Routing Is Configured\n\nThis is a **React** application using **React Router v6** (`react-router-dom`) with **Firebase Authentication**. Routing is set up across three key files:\n\n---\n\n#### 1. Route Definitions — `src/config/routes.js`\n\nRoutes are declared as a plain JavaScript array of objects:\n\n```js\nconst routes = [\n  {\n    path: \"\",\n    component: Home,\n    name: \"Home Page\",\n    protected: true,    // ← requires authentication\n  },\n  {\n    path: \"/login\",\n    component: Login,\n    name: \"Login Screen\",\n    protected: false,   // ← public\n  },\n];\n```\n\nEach route specifies:\n- **`path`** — the URL path (empty string = root `/`)\n- **`component`** — the React component to render\n- **`protected`** — a boolean flag that gates access behind authentication\n\n---\n\n#### 2. Route Rendering — `src/App.js`\n\nThe `App` component iterates over the routes array and renders `<Route>` elements. The critical logic is in the `element` prop:\n\n```jsx\n<Route\n  key={index}\n  path={route.path}\n  element={\n    route.protected ? (\n      <AuthChecker>\n        <route.component />\n      </AuthChecker>\n    ) : (\n      <route.component />\n    )\n  }\n/>\n```\n\n- If `protected` is **`true`**, the component is wrapped inside `<AuthChecker>`.\n- If `protected` is **`false`**, the component is rendered directly with no guard.\n\n---\n\n#### 3. Authentication Guard — `src/components/auth/AuthChecker.js`\n\nThis component acts as the **route guard** for protected routes:\n\n```jsx\nconst AuthChecker = ({ children }) => {\n  const navigate = useNavigate();\n\n  useEffect(() => {\n    if (!auth.currentUser) {\n      navigate(\"/login\");   // redirect unauthenticated users\n    }\n  }, []);\n\n  return <>{children}</>;\n};\n```\n\nWhen a user navigates to a protected route, `AuthChecker` checks Firebase's `auth.currentUser`. If no user is signed in, it **redirects immediately to `/login`**. If a user is authenticated, it renders the child component (the protected page) normally.\n\n---\n\n### Which Route Requires Authentication?\n\n| Route | Path | Protected? | Authentication Required? |\n|-------|------|------------|--------------------------|\n| **Home** | `\"/\"` (root) | `true` | ✅ **Yes** — must be signed in |\n| **Login** | `\"/login\"` | `false` | ❌ **No** — public |\n\n- **Home (`/`)** is the **protected route**. It requires the user to be authenticated. If an unauthenticated user tries to access it, `AuthChecker` redirects them to `/login`.\n- **Login (`/login`)** is the **public route**. Anyone can access it without being signed in. It displays a \"Sign In With Google\" button and a tabbed interface (Login / Register). After successful sign-in, the user is navigated back to the root route (`/`).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 938, "prompt_tokens": 9920, "total_tokens": 10858, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 267, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 9216}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 9216, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 704}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-pro", "system_fingerprint": "fp_9954b31ca7_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "b96453d5-ff19-4d92-b641-bf6ca109465a", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea579-ecce-7d81-be55-5feb8e18acab-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 9920, "output_tokens": 938, "total_tokens": 10858, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 9216}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 267}}}}]}}}
